    • Field Detail

      • PARAMETER_NAME_PATTERN

        static final Pattern PARAMETER_NAME_PATTERN
        Pattern used for parameter name validation. Must only consist of word characters or dashes - no spaces no special characters. Name must start with a letter, then it may contain any word character (including '-' and '_') and ends with a word character (no '-' or '_'), for instance:
         "abc"       - OK
 "foo-bar-0" - OK
 "013"       - NOT OK
 "foo-_bar"  - NOT OK
 "foo-bar"-  - NOT OK
        Since:
        2.12

      • PARAMETER_NAME_VERIFIER

        static final InputVerifier PARAMETER_NAME_VERIFIER
        Input verifier for swing component, such as text field, that checks against PARAMETER_NAME_PATTERN.
        Since:
        2.12

      • createEmptyDialogValue

        VAL createEmptyDialogValue()
        Used by the framework to create an empty and uninitialized dialog value instance. This is then kept, for instance in the subnode with updated user selected values. (Load & Save will be called to fill content.)
        Returns:
        A new empty instance of the dialog value class, not null.

      • setDialogValue

        void setDialogValue(VAL value)
        Loads a value edited outside the node into the node. 'Outside' here refers to the dialog of a sub- or meta node.
        Parameters:
        value - A value whose content should be used in the next calls of configure and execute. May be null to fall back to the defaults (as per configuration).

      • validateDialogValue

        void validateDialogValue(VAL value)
                  throws InvalidSettingsException
        Called prior setting a new dialog value. Implements can make sanity checks on the argument. Calling this method does not change the state/value set in the node.
        Parameters:
        value - The validate - not null.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - If invalid.
        Since:
        2.12

      • getParameterName

        String getParameterName()
        A simple name that is associated with this node for external parameterization. This is for instance used in command line control or when parameters are set via a web service invocation (that is, the workflow itself is the web service implementation). The returned value must not be null. An empty string is discouraged and only used for backward compatibility reasons (workflows saved prior 2.12 do not have this property).
        Returns:
        Parameter name used for external parameterization. Result must match PARAMETER_NAME_PATTERN
        Since:
        2.12

      • isHideInDialog

        boolean isHideInDialog()
        Property set in the configuration dialog of the node to hide this quickform/dialog node in the meta or subnode dialog.
        Returns:
        that property.
